This paper is about evolving controllers for legged robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of dynamic genotype-phenotype mapping and optimization, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions simulations and testing on a real-world robot, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
